Sentencas: Both the electrical conductivity and mechanical strength of a Sr0.8La0.2TiO3-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (SLT-GDC) composite decreased non-linearly as the GDC content increased.
Titulo: Percolation effect on electrical, mechanical, and electrochemical properties of Sr0.8La0.2TiO3-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the GDC percolation region, the electrical conductivity and the mechanical strength decreased significantly.
Titulo: Percolation effect on electrical, mechanical, and electrochemical properties of Sr0.8La0.2TiO3-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Because the carbon deposition rate increased with increasing GDC content, the redox stability decreased.
Titulo: Percolation effect on electrical, mechanical, and electrochemical properties of Sr0.8La0.2TiO3-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of the SLT-GDC composite anode at 800 degrees C in H-2 decreased up to 15 vol.% GDC (SLT-GDC15) and then increased at the SLT-GDC20 and the SLT-GDC33 compositions, due to the high electro-catalytic activity and low electrical conductivity of GDC.
Titulo: Percolation effect on electrical, mechanical, and electrochemical properties of Sr0.8La0.2TiO3-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Consequently, the SLT-GDC15 composition within the mixed region below SLT and GDC percolation limit exhibited the best electrochemical performance due to the optimized electronic and ionic conduction network.
Titulo: Percolation effect on electrical, mechanical, and electrochemical properties of Sr0.8La0.2TiO3-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 composite anodes for solid oxide fuel cells
